      <sec id="article-136349.s3" sec-type="Etiology">
        <title>Etiology</title>
        <p>The etiology of dyslipidemias is divided into primary and secondary causes.&#x000a0;&#x000a0;</p>
        <p>
<bold>Primary Dyslipidemias</bold>
</p>
        <p>These are a group of disorders caused by genetic defects in the synthesis, transport, or metabolism of lipoproteins and are typically present in childhood. These defects can be&#x000a0;monogenic or polygenic.<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="article-136349.r6">[6]</xref> A list of primary dyslipidemia is summarized:</p>
